  "subject": "Add bean validator based on javax.validation",
  "commit_message": "Add bean validator based on javax.validation\n\nAdded a new bean validator that uses the javax.validation API.  The\noriginal validator and its associated annotations will be left in the\nsource code until the other repos have been modified to use the new\nvalidator.\nUses hierarchical format for messages, as that facilitated adding nested\nmessages to the results.\nModified the old validator to support both annotation types.\nNote: in javax.validation, the NotBlank annotation has an implicit\nNotNull check, while the validator in policy-common does not.  Added a\nNullNotBlank annotation that can be used instead where the old behavior\nis needed.\nNote: in some cases, it appeared that class-level support of NotNull may\nnot be available with javax.validation.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-2059-javax-valid\nChange-Id: I2111e985d9725313fb3818ecc7fa62732aa040ee\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
